   There are four municipal golf courses: Harding (18-hole;
6,536-yard, par 72), where there's also a full-size driving range;
Roosevelt (nine-hole; 2,400-yard, par 33); Wilson (18-hole;
6,942-yard, par 72); and Los Feliz, a par-three course that's scruffy
and perfect for beginners. The Tregnan Golf Academy, a program run in
conjunction with the city of Los Angeles, offers golf clinics, camps
and tournaments to kids 7 to 18, regardless of ability.

   Cost: Dinner appetizers, $6 to $16; oysters, $14 a dozen;
shellfish and seafood tiers, $28 (for one to two people) to $99 (for
five to six); main courses, $16 to $42.

